World Bank to Grant Credit for Preserving Romania 's
BUCHAREST , December 23 ( Xinhua ) -- The World Bank will grant a loan of 4.9 million U.S. dollars for the financing of projects to preserve Romania 's cultural heritage .
According to a Wednesday report of Rompres news agency , the funds are intended to refurbish and restore the group of world-famous sculptures by Constantin Brancusi which are displayed in the artist 's home town , Tirgu Jiu of western Romania , to completely restore the Brancoveanu Palace , close to Bucharest , and other important cultural objectives .
Beginning 1990 , the World Bank granted Romania 2.7 billion U.S. dollars worth of loans for 21 projects .
